## What is this?

A minimal-API service on **.NET 8** (`Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web`). The layout keeps
logic pure and hostable code thin:

- `src/Api/Program.cs` — the wiring: builds the host and maps `GET /health`.
- `src/Api/StatusInfo.cs` — the pure, deterministic payload builder (no I/O,
  no clock), unit-tested without hosting the app.
- `tests/Api.Tests/` — xUnit test project referencing `src/Api`.

Both projects compile with `Nullable` **enabled** and warnings **as errors**.

## Quickstart

```bash
dotnet test tests/Api.Tests/Api.Tests.csproj    # restore + build + run tests
dotnet run --project src/Api                    # start the API
curl localhost:5000/health
```

{% if layout == 'monolith' %}## CI

These commands are wired into the root smart pipeline per service — no
`.github/` directory exists at this level on purpose.
{% else %}## CI

Three self-contained checks run on every push and PR — **build**, **test**,
**validate** (build with `-warnaserror`) — on the .NET 8 SDK. The platform's
reusable workflows are Python-focused; .NET CI is self-contained per SPEC §14.
{% endif %}

## Testing standard

Keep domain logic in pure, static, deterministic helpers like `StatusInfo` and
pin their invariants with exhaustive xUnit `[Theory]` tables
(`tests/Api.Tests/StatusInfoTests.cs`): blank-input normalisation, edge
trimming, version fallback and determinism. Add FsCheck if a helper's input
space outgrows tables.
